net.floodlightcontroller.core.internal

Class TableFeatures

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.floodlightcontroller.core.internal.TableFeatures

  • public class TableFeatures
extends java.lang.Object
    A small, immutable container for organizing the features of a particular table on a switch. OFTableFeatures is pretty much the same, but it doesn't easily expose the properties for quick access. This class will sacrifice the added time to instantiate instead of during each access to a particular property. Had the properties been in a Map of some sort, this might not be necessary. The assumption is that we won't ever change switch table properties frequently. It's more of a setup/initialization task. Otherwise, frequently making these would be quite inefficient considering the amount of data within and the number of tables switches can have. FIXME: OFTableFeatureProp types don't override equals in Loxi...
